  "text": "The constraints in (12) belong to chance-constrained vector inequalities, which are generally known to be computationally intractable [CITATION_1] , as we will also see later. In what follows, the goal is to derive equivalent deterministic expressions for (12) . For this purpose, we first need to study the statistical properties of the uncertain vector q k . We begin with the Gaussian error vector vec(E k ) of which the mean and the covariance matrix are respectively given by",
